properties.NAME: Dutchman Creek
properties.Info: Dutchman Creek is located between Warm Springs Creek and Lost Creek. The upper portion of the historic Dutchman Creek channel has long since become disconnected from the lower portion of the channel by irrigation infrastructure construction. The lower portion of Dutchman Creek, which flows through the West-central portion of the Dutchman, is fed by shallow ground water as it migrates downgradient to the east.

properties.NAME: Lost Creek
properties.Info: Lost Creek is a relatively small drainage that encompasses an area of approximately 25 square miles. It is located north of Anaconda and enters the Clark Fork River near Galen. Lost Creek enters the Dutchman Wetlands near the Northeastern property boundary, and flows into the Dutchman Pond. Lost Creek flows downstream of the Pond follow the historic stream channel to the Clark Fork River. Although a much smaller stream, the lower portions of Lost Creek present fishing opportunities for smaller trout species, as well as wildlife viewing for animals utilizing the stream corridor.

properties.NAME: Warm Springs Creek
properties.Info: Warm Springs Creek is a major drainage basin that originates in the Pintler and Flint Creek ranges west of Anaconda and drains an area of approximately 163 square miles and is a main tributary stream of the Clark Fork River. Warm Springs Creek has an approximate 11-mile reach within the ARWW&S OU, a portion of which has been remediated and reconstructed as part of the ARWW&S OU Superfund Remedy. Most species of trout common to the upper Clark Fork River can be found throughout Warm Springs Creek.
